<div id='communityQuestionsWithAnswers'>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/2004071-i-am-generally-sensitive-to-animal-abuse">I am generally sensitive to animal abuse, but I know it is necessary to be aware and educated. Will this book be too upsetting for someone like me?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_2004071'><a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F29380.Animal_Liberation">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/2004071-i-am-generally-sensitive-to-animal-abuse">one year ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/2004071-i-am-generally-sensitive-to-animal-abuse">See all 2 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/141479182-avigayil"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1639168931i/141479182._UX100_CR0,8,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/141479182-avigayil">Avigayil</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Many of the descriptions are direct excerpts from farming magazines or research studies, and it is all factually described with very little gratuitous<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Many of the descriptions are direct excerpts from farming magazines or research studies, and it is all factually described with very little gratuitous detail or emotional appeal. I still had to put the book down multiple times, nauseated. I think if you do purchase meat/eggs/dairy from grocery stores, or use animal-tested products (e.g. shampoo that is not cruelty-free), it is very much worth a read to understand what your money goes towards. I will add a caveat, which is that from what I remember, the revised edition is not absolutely clear on whether the practices it describes have changed at all since the original edition, and I am not sufficiently educated to say whether they are (though from the little of the exposés I do know, such practices have been far from eradicated). If you'd like to avoid the more explicit descriptions of abuse, you could simply skip over most of the chapters on the farm and research industries, and read the introduction and the chapters on the arguments for/against animal liberation. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

<div class='flagAnswer'>
<a class="right flag" rel="nofollow" id="flag_link1240149" title="Flag this answer as inappropriate." href="/flagged/new?resource_id=1240149&amp;resource_type=CommunityAnswer&amp;return_url=%2Fquestions%2F2004071-i-am-generally-sensitive-to-animal-abuse%2Fanswers%2F1240149-many-of-the">flag</a>
</div>
<ul class='communityQAFooter answerFooter'>
</ul>

</div>
