        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3237253078" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17256370979275757424">This is one of the earliest books in the animal rights movement that was written way back in 1975 and revised later on. I really appreciate the author&apos;s grit in seeing the reality of the speciesist mindset of us humans and investigating the various ways in which animals are exploited; be it in psychiatric or chemical testing and especially to satisfy our palates. Most of these topics are so gruesome and disturbing that I had to intentionally skip reading those pages, but we cannot deny the fact </span>
  <span id="freeText17256370979275757424" style="display:none">This is one of the earliest books in the animal rights movement that was written way back in 1975 and revised later on. I really appreciate the author's grit in seeing the reality of the speciesist mindset of us humans and investigating the various ways in which animals are exploited; be it in psychiatric or chemical testing and especially to satisfy our palates. Most of these topics are so gruesome and disturbing that I had to intentionally skip reading those pages, but we cannot deny the fact that this is what is happening in reality. This book is definitely an eye opener in several aspects. </span>
